/* Well, it is all about stream style. Some content changes:
Google post their trash like communities, trends etc as divs with uniquie
data-iid tag. It was so before and was not changed. Some new id:
sii2:111 - new post form
sii2:102 - "Trending"
sii2:103 - "You may know"
sii2:105 - "Interesting people and other shit"
sii2:106 - "You might like"
sii2:112 - "communities invitations"
sii2:116 - "maybe you know"
Say if you find more.
In the old version it was 13 for trends, 33 - you might like, 34 - fun & interesting, not sure about now, maybe sii2:1xx?
*/
div[data-iid="sii2:102"], div[data-iid="sii2:103"],
div[data-iid="sii2:105"], div[data-iid="sii2:106"], 
div[data-iid="sii2:112"], div[data-iid="sii2:116"] {
display: none;
}
